  "active_lock_reason": null,
  "body": "Currently we assume the algo is RSA but there's no reason for this restriction. \r\nIn theory, we can support whatever algorithms the JWT spec and Vertx can support. The JWT protocol allows for the use of much stronger algorithms that can be executed by virtually any major cryptographic library (OpenSSL, libgcrypt, NaCL, libsodium, Botan, etc.)\r\n\r\nWill require a docs change since we specifically mention RSA: https://besu.hyperledger.org/en/stable/HowTo/Interact/APIs/Authentication/",
