    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Did some further research on this, came across this article https://auth0.com/blog/critical-vulnerabilities-in-json-web-token-libraries/\r\n\r\nSeems like there have been past attacks taking advantage of the different signing algorithms.. Although that definitely seems to have been fixed since. \r\n\r\nThe author seems to think the `alg` field on JWTs should be deprecated at a JWT standard level and backend applications should be passing the algorithm used to JWT libraries. (As far as I can tell this hasn't been adopted and there are definitely APIs out there that accept many signing algorithms)\r\n\r\nYour thoughts @macfarla ?\r\n",
